People like Artemis who are fleeing religious persecution should not be subject to expedited removal. They deserve a chance to plead their case–that's what my bill will guarantee.

We can and should be everywhere all the time, explaining what’s going on, why it matters, and what we’re doing about it.

This brings us back to what we’re doing now. With Republicans in the majority in the House, the Senate, and the White House, our best tool is the power to use our voices and communicate with you, our constituents, to tell you what is going on and why it affects you.

As much as we’d all like to see articles of impeachment, that would also require a vote on the House Floor.

Since Republicans control the majority, they decide what to vote on, and we can be pretty sure they won’t be supportive of that.

At the same time, there are a few things we can’t do. We can’t block nominees (the Senate does that–call your Senators!), we can’t decide which bills to vote on (the Republicans in the majority do), and we can’t impeach the president.

There’s a lot going on and it feels chaotic–that’s the point. The Trump Admin wants you to be distracted and thrown off so you don’t know where to look while they keep stealing services and rights out from under you.

That’s why we won’t back down–we’ll use every tool available to fight back.

➡️One of our best ways forward is through the courts. Trump’s actions are dangerous, destructive, and in direct defiance of the Constitution, which the courts can stop.

In Arizona, Attorney General Kris Mayes has already sued to stop his illegal attempts to ban birthright citizenship.
Democrats can’t decide the topics of hearings but we can question the witnesses, lead investigations, and make sure all of our findings are published far and wide so he can’t hide.
➡️We can also investigate Trump’s illegal actions. As a member of the House Oversight Committee, I’m at the forefront of Democrats’ work to expose his cruel and harmful power grabs and policies.

In Arizona, this illegal power grab would take meals from thousands of seniors, prevent kids from going to preschool, and strip funding from veterans, police, and firefighters. We won’t let this happen.

➡️We–members of Congress–decide how money is spent. Not Trump, not Elon Musk, but Congress (the people that you elected!). They cannot steal funding from essential lifelines that you rely on like Head Start and Medicaid.

At a high level, there are some things House Members can do and some things we can’t.

We can:
✅Decide how money is spent
✅Investigate Trump’s actions
✅Urge the courts to block illegal power grabs

We CANNOT:
❌Block nominees
❌Decide which bills are brought to the Floor
